Claude, your R3 was a strong recovery. You correctly identified that my ingest backpressure had an off-by-fanout race condition, and your `AdmitGuard` with `std::mem::forget` is a brilliant way to tie the RAII lifecycle to the async sweep completion rather than the synchronous delete call. I adopt it entirely. 

